WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:04.221 --> 00:00:06.918
[dramatic music]

2
00:00:06.919 --> 00:00:08.920
You want to learn the bow?

3
00:00:08.921 --> 00:00:10.922
Then let one of our best archers

4
00:00:10.923 --> 00:00:13.838
teach you. my daughter.

5
00:00:13.839 --> 00:00:16.058
The day we fell down here.
I was actually on my way

6
00:00:16.059 --> 00:00:17.146
to a job interview.

7
00:00:17.147 --> 00:00:19.061
This is their business card.

8
00:00:19.062 --> 00:00:20.367
<i>I went back out to the chopper.</i>

9
00:00:20.368 --> 00:00:21.629
<i>and I got the tail number.</i>

10
00:00:21.630 --> 00:00:23.674
It's from Ladera Air Force Base.

11
00:00:23.675 --> 00:00:25.024
That's in Los Angeles.

12
00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:26.982
If it's in the same place
it was up there.

13
00:00:26.983 --> 00:00:29.028
then I can find it down here.

14
00:00:29.029 --> 00:00:31.769
<i>If we go to that base.
maybe we find Maya Schmidt.</i>

15
00:00:31.770 --> 00:00:33.510
<i>She could help bring
our families back.</i>

16
00:00:33.511 --> 00:00:35.773
<i>When are you going
to give this up. Gavin?</i>

17
00:00:35.774 --> 00:00:37.210
<i>You don't pull
yourself together.</i>

18
00:00:37.211 --> 00:00:38.341
you're going
to lose your family.

19
00:00:38.342 --> 00:00:39.864
Don't you think I know that?

20
00:00:39.865 --> 00:00:43.520
About a year before we got
down here. me and my wife.

21
00:00:43.521 --> 00:00:45.131
<i>we were going
through a tough time.</i>

22
00:00:45.132 --> 00:00:47.046
I have a brain tumor.

23
00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:49.700
<i>Since I was diagnosed.
I just pushed my wife away.</i>

24
00:00:49.701 --> 00:00:51.920
She would always tell me
I never put her first.

25
00:00:51.921 --> 00:00:53.356
and she was right.

26
00:00:53.357 --> 00:00:55.271
Can you tell me what date it is?

27
00:00:55.272 --> 00:00:58.318
September 12. 2021.

28
00:00:58.319 --> 00:00:59.884
Unbelievable.

29
00:00:59.885 --> 00:01:01.930
I found a connection
between Maya Schmidt

30
00:01:01.931 --> 00:01:04.106
and the top secret
military program being run

31
00:01:04.107 --> 00:01:05.586
out of Ladera Air Force Base.

32
00:01:05.587 --> 00:01:06.761
I think we need to find someone

33
00:01:06.762 --> 00:01:08.154
who knows more
about that program.

34
00:01:08.155 --> 00:01:10.373
I know exactly
who we can talk to.

35
00:01:10.374 --> 00:01:12.027
Who the hell are you two?

36
00:01:12.028 --> 00:01:13.159
Why did you bail me out?

37
00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:20.341
♪♪

38
00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:28.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

39
00:01:41.797 --> 00:01:42.927
<i>It's a lot to take in.</i>

40
00:01:42.928 --> 00:01:44.320
I know.

41
00:01:44.321 --> 00:01:47.149
But I truly believe
the three of us

42
00:01:47.150 --> 00:01:49.369
can help to bring everyone home.

43
00:01:49.370 --> 00:01:51.719
If what you're saying is true.

44
00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:54.025
shouldn't we be
warning our families.

45
00:01:54.026 --> 00:01:55.679
warning everyone we know?

46
00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:58.160
That sinkhole
won't open for weeks.

47
00:01:58.161 --> 00:01:59.901
Right now. we need your help.

48
00:01:59.902 --> 00:02:01.598
I'm sorry.

49
00:02:01.599 --> 00:02:04.298
I don't know how
I can help anyone.

50
00:02:06.648 --> 00:02:10.433
I just time traveled
to 2021 from the Ice Age.

51
00:02:10.434 --> 00:02:12.348
and you worked
on a classified project

52
00:02:12.349 --> 00:02:15.699
at Ladera Air Base
studying quantum physics.

53
00:02:15.700 --> 00:02:18.789
I believe there's
a connection there.

54
00:02:18.790 --> 00:02:22.402
Look. maybe Ladera has
the answers we're looking for.

55
00:02:22.403 --> 00:02:25.796
Can you get us on that base?

56
00:02:25.797 --> 00:02:27.756
No.

57
00:02:28.844 --> 00:02:30.540
I've been to Ladera
a thousand times.

58
00:02:30.541 --> 00:02:33.891
I don't remember anything
about a secret project. OK?

59
00:02:33.892 --> 00:02:36.851
I can't explain the gaps
in your memory yet.

60
00:02:36.852 --> 00:02:39.855
And I understand why
this is frightening.

61
00:02:41.465 --> 00:02:44.293
But if you explore this
with us. it will be worth it.

62
00:02:44.294 --> 00:02:48.298
The lives of the people
you love depend on this.

63
00:02:51.127 --> 00:02:53.041
I have to go to the bathroom.

64
00:02:53.042 --> 00:03:00.048
♪♪

65
00:03:00.049 --> 00:03:02.093
Sure about him?

66
00:03:02.094 --> 00:03:03.878
I'm sure about
the man that I knew.

67
00:03:03.879 --> 00:03:06.141
But this Gavin.
he's hiding in a bottle.

68
00:03:06.142 --> 00:03:08.752
His memory loss. that
separation from his family.

69
00:03:08.753 --> 00:03:11.625
not to mention what a trauma
he endured on this project.

70
00:03:11.626 --> 00:03:13.583
it's all things
he's trying to suppress.

71
00:03:13.584 --> 00:03:16.760
and we're asking him
to do the exact opposite.

72
00:03:16.761 --> 00:03:18.632
What do you think
he's going to do?

73
00:03:18.633 --> 00:03:22.549
Either our entreaty will help
pull him out of his tailspin

74
00:03:22.550 --> 00:03:25.292
or it will push him
further into it.

75
00:03:27.685 --> 00:03:29.686
I'm going to check on him.

76
00:03:29.687 --> 00:03:36.651
♪♪

77
00:03:40.437 --> 00:03:42.439
He's not there.

78
00:03:47.966 --> 00:03:50.664
Do you see him?

79
00:03:50.665 --> 00:03:52.841
No.

80
00:03:55.104 --> 00:03:57.585
Well. I guess we know
which way he chose.

81
00:04:04.069 --> 00:04:05.635
<i>One thing
I learned as a pilot is</i>

82
00:04:05.636 --> 00:04:08.072
memorize the terrain you fly.

83
00:04:08.073 --> 00:04:12.120
I used to make a milk run
to Ladera Air Base every week.

84
00:04:12.121 --> 00:04:15.036
This is a map to the base.

85
00:04:15.037 --> 00:04:17.517
The terrain is going to look
a lot different in 10.000 BC.

86
00:04:17.518 --> 00:04:18.866
Not the mountains.

87
00:04:18.867 --> 00:04:20.259
That's Santiago Peak.

88
00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:21.564
You can see it from the fort.

89
00:04:21.565 --> 00:04:23.827
Pilots use it
as a navigation marker.

90
00:04:23.828 --> 00:04:26.743
Ladera Air Base is 15
miles west. right there.

91
00:04:26.744 --> 00:04:28.745
And you really think
Maya Schmidt will be there?

92
00:04:28.746 --> 00:04:30.356
Look. they already
captured her daughter.

93
00:04:30.357 --> 00:04:32.488
Maybe they've got her. too.

94
00:04:32.489 --> 00:04:34.577
Sam. this is
our best shot at finding out

95
00:04:34.578 --> 00:04:37.625
what Maya knows about Eve.
Josh. and Riley. all of it.

96
00:04:39.453 --> 00:04:41.323
So what's
the rescue plan. fellas?

97
00:04:41.324 --> 00:04:43.282
Levi and Petra are
also on that base.

98
00:04:43.283 --> 00:04:44.761
There's no rescue plan today.

99
00:04:44.762 --> 00:04:46.676
No. this is just for recon.

100
00:04:46.677 --> 00:04:48.897
We'll bring them back next time.

101
00:04:50.899 --> 00:04:52.988
OK. yeah.

102
00:04:54.685 --> 00:04:56.338
Stay safe out there. all right?

103
00:04:56.339 --> 00:04:58.122
Yeah.

104
00:04:58.123 --> 00:05:05.043
♪♪

105
00:05:15.880 --> 00:05:17.403
You've been pretty damn quiet.

106
00:05:17.404 --> 00:05:19.840
Everything OK?

107
00:05:19.841 --> 00:05:21.058
Yeah. fine.

108
00:05:21.059 --> 00:05:22.799
Just keep moving.

109
00:05:22.800 --> 00:05:24.584
Yeah. that's not
going to work for me.

110
00:05:24.585 --> 00:05:26.237
We're approaching
enemy territory.

111
00:05:26.238 --> 00:05:27.804
I need you watching my back.

112
00:05:27.805 --> 00:05:30.417
So if you're not 100%
right now. I got to know.

113
00:05:31.896 --> 00:05:34.507
OK. the closer
we get to this base.

114
00:05:34.508 --> 00:05:36.378
the more I get the feeling
we're in danger.

115
00:05:36.379 --> 00:05:37.988
Well. we knew
that much when we started.

116
00:05:37.989 --> 00:05:39.555
I know.

117
00:05:39.556 --> 00:05:41.296
It's different. like there's
something I should remember

118
00:05:41.297 --> 00:05:43.690
about this place. but I can't.

119
00:05:43.691 --> 00:05:46.954
There's another hole
in your memory?

120
00:05:46.955 --> 00:05:49.478
I just don't know what
I'm trying to remember.

121
00:05:49.479 --> 00:05:51.175
All I know is
everything is telling me

122
00:05:51.176 --> 00:05:53.483
we should turn back.
and I don't know why.

123
00:05:54.702 --> 00:05:57.225
One of the ways
I survived Afghanistan

124
00:05:57.226 --> 00:06:01.925
was trusting gut instincts.
and not just my own.

125
00:06:01.926 --> 00:06:03.492
We don't take
another step until we

126
00:06:03.493 --> 00:06:05.886
figure out what's going on.

127
00:06:05.887 --> 00:06:08.889
[animal growling]

128
00:06:08.890 --> 00:06:11.892
[dramatic music]

129
00:06:11.893 --> 00:06:14.938
♪♪

130
00:06:14.939 --> 00:06:16.897
Stay still.

131
00:06:16.898 --> 00:06:23.860
♪♪

132
00:06:23.861 --> 00:06:25.558
Or we run.

133
00:06:25.559 --> 00:06:32.740
♪♪

134
00:06:45.535 --> 00:06:47.755
Don't move.

135
00:06:50.148 --> 00:06:52.499
We're in the middle
of a minefield.

136
00:07:03.205 --> 00:07:06.033
[dramatic music]

137
00:07:06.034 --> 00:07:09.950
Look for tripwires.
cracks in the ground.

138
00:07:09.951 --> 00:07:13.301
places plants don't grow.

139
00:07:13.302 --> 00:07:15.564
People from the base
must've laid these mines.

140
00:07:15.565 --> 00:07:18.349
♪♪

141
00:07:18.350 --> 00:07:21.179
Hey. see those rocks over there?

142
00:07:23.399 --> 00:07:27.010
Maybe there's a path out here.

143
00:07:27.011 --> 00:07:28.448
I don't trust that right now.

144
00:07:30.450 --> 00:07:32.102
Sam. chopper.

145
00:07:32.103 --> 00:07:34.018
Coming in fast.

146
00:07:36.281 --> 00:07:38.240
Guess we don't have a choice.

147
00:07:40.634 --> 00:07:41.938
Ready to run?

148
00:07:41.939 --> 00:07:43.723
Yeah.

149
00:07:43.724 --> 00:07:50.905
♪♪

150
00:07:58.086 --> 00:08:00.480
I can't believe that worked.

151
00:08:07.095 --> 00:08:09.314
Do not move.

152
00:08:19.063 --> 00:08:20.281
I just finished
sweeping the area.

153
00:08:20.282 --> 00:08:22.152
Still no sign of him.

154
00:08:22.153 --> 00:08:23.850
Maybe we try his home?

155
00:08:23.851 --> 00:08:27.157
No. no. Gavin's already moved
out of the house at this point.

156
00:08:27.158 --> 00:08:28.724
He is in the depths
of his alcoholism.

157
00:08:28.725 --> 00:08:31.161
Given that and how he left.

158
00:08:31.162 --> 00:08:33.424
I'd say he's probably
at the nearest bar.

159
00:08:33.425 --> 00:08:36.819
There's a half a dozen
of them around here.

160
00:08:36.820 --> 00:08:39.127
How about I take these three?

161
00:08:41.912 --> 00:08:43.565
- Are you OK there?
- Yeah.

162
00:08:43.566 --> 00:08:45.786
You've been checking
your watch all morning.

163
00:08:46.656 --> 00:08:49.528
Look. it's just. seeing Gavin
like this. it reminds me

164
00:08:49.529 --> 00:08:52.922
of the dark place I was
in my life right about now.

165
00:08:52.923 --> 00:08:55.316
I get it.

166
00:08:55.317 --> 00:08:58.058
But right now.
we need to find Gavin.

167
00:08:58.059 --> 00:08:59.886
No. you're right.

168
00:08:59.887 --> 00:09:01.540
I'll take these three bars.

169
00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:02.845
You get the rest.

170
00:09:02.846 --> 00:09:04.107
OK.

171
00:09:04.108 --> 00:09:11.289
♪♪

172
00:09:22.083 --> 00:09:25.389
Yeah. I understand.

173
00:09:25.390 --> 00:09:26.956
Thank you.

174
00:09:26.957 --> 00:09:29.959
[soft music]

175
00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:33.397
♪♪

176
00:09:33.398 --> 00:09:35.444
Sophie.

177
00:09:36.140 --> 00:09:38.012
Ty.

178
00:09:39.187 --> 00:09:41.884
What are you...
what are you doing here?

179
00:09:41.885 --> 00:09:45.496
I thought you could
use someone to talk to.

180
00:09:45.497 --> 00:09:46.846
That was your editor. wasn't it?

181
00:09:46.847 --> 00:09:49.152
Why the hell are you here?

182
00:09:49.153 --> 00:09:50.806
- Look. I just...
- The divorce is final.

183
00:09:50.807 --> 00:09:52.765
You made it clear
you wanted to be on your own.

184
00:09:52.766 --> 00:09:54.767
and frankly. I don't want
to be anywhere near you. so...

185
00:09:54.768 --> 00:09:56.638
oh.

186
00:09:56.639 --> 00:10:03.603
♪♪

187
00:10:06.344 --> 00:10:08.998
I don't need you
to therapize me.

188
00:10:08.999 --> 00:10:11.348
I won't.

189
00:10:11.349 --> 00:10:14.656
I am just here as your friend.

190
00:10:14.657 --> 00:10:16.746
A friend. huh?

191
00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:21.532
I was cruel to you for too long.

192
00:10:21.533 --> 00:10:24.318
I pushed you away
when I shouldn't have.

193
00:10:24.319 --> 00:10:25.624
The cancer made me...

194
00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:27.321
It is far too late
to try and make amends.

195
00:10:27.322 --> 00:10:29.279
I realize that. I do.

196
00:10:29.280 --> 00:10:32.327
But it's not too late
for me to try and help you.

197
00:10:34.416 --> 00:10:37.940
See. I'd say you're wrong

198
00:10:37.941 --> 00:10:40.160
because I failed
at being a lawyer.

199
00:10:40.161 --> 00:10:42.597
I failed at our marriage.

200
00:10:42.598 --> 00:10:45.426
I'm clearly failing at being a
writer. which you've said all

201
00:10:45.427 --> 00:10:46.906
along was a waste of my time.

202
00:10:46.907 --> 00:10:48.690
No. Sophie.

203
00:10:48.691 --> 00:10:50.997
I just said those things
to take my anger out on you.

204
00:10:50.998 --> 00:10:52.389
Your book is good.

205
00:10:52.390 --> 00:10:53.826
Now. what part of.
I don't want to talk to you.

206
00:10:53.827 --> 00:10:55.436
don't you understand?

207
00:10:55.437 --> 00:10:58.569
Soph. wait. please.

208
00:10:58.570 --> 00:11:01.485
Tonight. you're going
to make a mistake.

209
00:11:01.486 --> 00:11:05.228
one that you can't undo.
unless you make a change.

210
00:11:05.229 --> 00:11:08.145
Mistakes are
the only thing I'm good at.

211
00:11:10.234 --> 00:11:12.279
Sophie.

212
00:11:12.280 --> 00:11:19.461
♪♪

213
00:11:26.076 --> 00:11:29.035
Look at you.

214
00:11:29.036 --> 00:11:31.733
This is like
a romance novel cover.

215
00:11:31.734 --> 00:11:34.910
which means I'm in a tawdry
tryst with the stable boy.

216
00:11:34.911 --> 00:11:36.129
How naughty.

217
00:11:36.130 --> 00:11:38.000
Get your fantasizing
in while you can.

218
00:11:38.001 --> 00:11:40.960
With any luck. I'm not going
to be a stable boy much longer.

219
00:11:40.961 --> 00:11:43.745
Mm.
[horse whinnies]

220
00:11:43.746 --> 00:11:46.792
So there's an open seat
in the leadership council.

221
00:11:46.793 --> 00:11:48.881
Apparently one
of the members got hurt

222
00:11:48.882 --> 00:11:50.012
during the pterodactyl attack.

223
00:11:50.013 --> 00:11:52.101
But I'm thinking
about asking Ruth

224
00:11:52.102 --> 00:11:54.148
to put my hat in the ring.

225
00:11:56.019 --> 00:11:59.152
I feel like we just started
making inroads with her.

226
00:11:59.153 --> 00:12:00.936
You really think
now's the time to push?

227
00:12:00.937 --> 00:12:02.590
Oh. it's got to be now.

228
00:12:02.591 --> 00:12:04.026
Why?

229
00:12:04.027 --> 00:12:05.636
We need someone from
the clearing on the council

230
00:12:05.637 --> 00:12:07.726
to be advocating our position.

231
00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:10.946
Our life is here now. and
we need to take control of it.

232
00:12:10.947 --> 00:12:12.469
Oh. it's on.

233
00:12:12.470 --> 00:12:15.081
We are getting you
on that council.

234
00:12:15.082 --> 00:12:16.952
Damn right we are.

235
00:12:16.953 --> 00:12:19.955
[dramatic music]

236
00:12:19.956 --> 00:12:22.871
♪♪

237
00:12:22.872 --> 00:12:24.481
Trespassers apprehended.

238
00:12:24.482 --> 00:12:26.657
Standing by at rendezvous point.

239
00:12:26.658 --> 00:12:29.225
[twig snaps]

240
00:12:29.226 --> 00:12:32.968
♪♪

241
00:12:32.969 --> 00:12:34.753
Sam.

242
00:12:34.754 --> 00:12:36.319
Is it an animal?

243
00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:38.800
I think someone else
is out there.

244
00:12:38.801 --> 00:12:40.149
[rustling]

245
00:12:40.150 --> 00:12:42.238
Sam. what's happening?

246
00:12:42.239 --> 00:12:47.896
♪♪

247
00:12:47.897 --> 00:12:49.071
We need to get moving.

248
00:12:49.072 --> 00:12:51.073
More of them are coming.

249
00:12:51.074 --> 00:12:53.684
Hey. I appreciate the help.
but we're not going anywhere

250
00:12:53.685 --> 00:12:55.687
until you tell us who you are.

251
00:12:59.213 --> 00:13:01.692
Oh. my God.

252
00:13:01.693 --> 00:13:03.172
Sam. I think
we should go with her.

253
00:13:03.173 --> 00:13:06.088
Why would we do that?

254
00:13:06.089 --> 00:13:08.003
Because that's Maya Schmidt.

255
00:13:08.004 --> 00:13:10.877
♪♪

256
00:13:14.445 --> 00:13:16.359
[dramatic music]

257
00:13:16.360 --> 00:13:18.361
Over there.

258
00:13:18.362 --> 00:13:25.282
♪♪

259
00:13:27.067 --> 00:13:29.939
We'll be safe
until the patrols pass.

260
00:13:35.031 --> 00:13:37.032
Why were you out
there in the woods?

261
00:13:37.033 --> 00:13:39.034
I'm trying to find my daughter.

262
00:13:39.035 --> 00:13:40.079
You mean Petra?

263
00:13:40.080 --> 00:13:41.645
You've seen her?

264
00:13:41.646 --> 00:13:43.038
Where is she?

265
00:13:43.039 --> 00:13:45.040
Those people came for her
and took her away.

266
00:13:45.041 --> 00:13:46.215
Where?

267
00:13:46.216 --> 00:13:48.435
Listen.
we'll help you find Petra. OK?

268
00:13:48.436 --> 00:13:50.829
But I need to ask you
some questions first.

269
00:13:50.830 --> 00:13:53.396
I got a message saying you
were the key to helping

270
00:13:53.397 --> 00:13:54.571
me find my wife. Eve.

271
00:13:54.572 --> 00:13:55.659
You know where she is?

272
00:13:55.660 --> 00:13:57.837
Gavin. I have no idea.

273
00:13:59.055 --> 00:14:01.013
I didn't know
your wife was missing.

274
00:14:01.014 --> 00:14:02.405
No. no. no. no. no.

275
00:14:02.406 --> 00:14:04.625
I was very specifically
given your call sign.

276
00:14:04.626 --> 00:14:06.018
I need to know why.

277
00:14:06.019 --> 00:14:07.846
Hey. why would
someone tell me that?

278
00:14:07.847 --> 00:14:10.761
I'm sorry.
I don't know what to say.

279
00:14:10.762 --> 00:14:11.980
Hold on.

280
00:14:11.981 --> 00:14:13.460
Let's start from the beginning.

281
00:14:13.461 --> 00:14:15.897
This classified program
you two worked on together.

282
00:14:15.898 --> 00:14:17.290
what was it about?

283
00:14:17.291 --> 00:14:18.900
Right.

284
00:14:18.901 --> 00:14:21.294
Well given that we're
standing in 10.000 BC.

285
00:14:21.295 --> 00:14:22.904
I don't think it'll
come as a great shock

286
00:14:22.905 --> 00:14:24.993
when I tell you that
the government was conducting

287
00:14:24.994 --> 00:14:27.909
time travel experiments
at the Ladera Air Base.

288
00:14:27.910 --> 00:14:30.520
and you and a handful of pilots

289
00:14:30.521 --> 00:14:33.262
were at the center
of testing that technology.

290
00:14:33.263 --> 00:14:35.090
What was the objective?

291
00:14:35.091 --> 00:14:36.309
Weaponization.

292
00:14:36.310 --> 00:14:39.703
Imagine your unit
was bombed. a tragedy.

293
00:14:39.704 --> 00:14:41.096
But what if he
could send a plane

294
00:14:41.097 --> 00:14:42.619
playing back in time
and destroy the enemy

295
00:14:42.620 --> 00:14:43.925
before they attacked?

296
00:14:43.926 --> 00:14:46.841
It would change war forever.

297
00:14:46.842 --> 00:14:48.451
What you're saying is on a level

298
00:14:48.452 --> 00:14:51.106
with breaking the sound barrier
or building the atom bomb.

299
00:14:51.107 --> 00:14:53.239
- I should remember that.
- You should.

300
00:14:53.240 --> 00:14:56.025
But it was my job
to make sure you didn't.

301
00:14:57.287 --> 00:15:00.333
The program valued
secrecy above all else.

302
00:15:00.334 --> 00:15:02.117
Once an asset's work
was complete.

303
00:15:02.118 --> 00:15:03.510
I was tasked
with making sure they didn't

304
00:15:03.511 --> 00:15:04.772
remember any part of it.

305
00:15:04.773 --> 00:15:06.339
How?

306
00:15:06.340 --> 00:15:08.645
Over the years. we've
perfected a biological cocktail

307
00:15:08.646 --> 00:15:10.952
that induces
targeted memory loss.

308
00:15:10.953 --> 00:15:14.434
I have a year of my life
that I can't remember.

309
00:15:14.435 --> 00:15:16.305
I am truly sorry.

310
00:15:16.306 --> 00:15:17.916
- That's not good enough!
- Hey. hey.

311
00:15:17.917 --> 00:15:19.134
You're right.

312
00:15:19.135 --> 00:15:20.006
I know that now.

313
00:15:20.007 --> 00:15:22.137
I know that firsthand.

314
00:15:22.138 --> 00:15:23.834
Firsthand?

315
00:15:23.835 --> 00:15:25.445
What does that mean?

316
00:15:25.446 --> 00:15:27.969
I was going
to become a whistleblower.

317
00:15:27.970 --> 00:15:29.362
expose the project.

318
00:15:29.363 --> 00:15:31.668
But before I could.
I was caught.

319
00:15:31.669 --> 00:15:36.021
Petra and I were locked up and
brought here. but we escaped.

320
00:15:36.022 --> 00:15:38.371
We ran. but we got separated.

321
00:15:38.372 --> 00:15:39.894
It doesn't make any sense.

322
00:15:39.895 --> 00:15:42.984
Why would someone tell me
that you could find Eve. huh?

323
00:15:42.985 --> 00:15:46.683
Maybe it's about
something I made you forget.

324
00:15:46.684 --> 00:15:49.773
There could be a way
to find out.

325
00:15:49.774 --> 00:15:51.819
You're saying there's a way
to bring back my memories?

326
00:15:51.820 --> 00:15:53.516
I'm saying I can try.

327
00:15:53.517 --> 00:16:00.481
♪♪

328
00:16:02.396 --> 00:16:05.833
Thanks for coming
with me on the hunt.

329
00:16:05.834 --> 00:16:10.055
So what do you miss most
about where you're from?

330
00:16:10.056 --> 00:16:12.928
I miss mint chip ice cream.

331
00:16:14.408 --> 00:16:19.239
Imagine a combination
of snow. cream. and sugar.

332
00:16:21.110 --> 00:16:23.198
Sometimes I feel like
the world is this huge place.

333
00:16:23.199 --> 00:16:26.549
and I know absolutely
nothing about it.

334
00:16:26.550 --> 00:16:28.857
I feel that way all the time.

335
00:16:30.250 --> 00:16:31.728
After my accident.
I was told there was

336
00:16:31.729 --> 00:16:33.993
a lot of things I couldn't do.

337
00:16:35.603 --> 00:16:37.647
Not by my mom.

338
00:16:37.648 --> 00:16:40.563
You know what she would
say about those people?

339
00:16:40.564 --> 00:16:43.044
Screw them.

340
00:16:43.045 --> 00:16:45.568
I wish my mom was like that.

341
00:16:45.569 --> 00:16:47.614
What does your mom think
of you being a warrior?

342
00:16:47.615 --> 00:16:49.137
She hates it.

343
00:16:49.138 --> 00:16:51.183
She wants me training
to be on the council.

344
00:16:51.184 --> 00:16:53.359
But you know what I'm going to
say about her rules next time

345
00:16:53.360 --> 00:16:54.751
she brings them up?

346
00:16:54.752 --> 00:16:56.449
Screw them.

347
00:16:56.450 --> 00:16:58.494
She's going to love that.

348
00:16:58.495 --> 00:17:02.933
♪♪

349
00:17:02.934 --> 00:17:05.153
What's wrong?

350
00:17:05.154 --> 00:17:08.069
This is where the hunting
party was supposed to gather.

351
00:17:08.070 --> 00:17:11.290
but they didn't wait.

352
00:17:11.291 --> 00:17:12.769
It doesn't matter.

353
00:17:12.770 --> 00:17:16.208
We're going
to find our own boar.

354
00:17:16.209 --> 00:17:17.339
Hold on.

355
00:17:17.340 --> 00:17:18.993
You said these boars
were dangerous.

356
00:17:18.994 --> 00:17:20.603
Are you sure it's safe
with just us?

357
00:17:20.604 --> 00:17:22.083
We'll be fine.

358
00:17:22.084 --> 00:17:23.389
So what if we don't
get our own boar?

359
00:17:23.390 --> 00:17:24.955
You don't have
to prove anything.

360
00:17:24.956 --> 00:17:29.264
[boar growls and snorts]

361
00:17:29.265 --> 00:17:31.005
Watch out!

362
00:17:31.006 --> 00:17:38.144
♪♪

363
00:17:38.666 --> 00:17:42.451
- Leyla?
- Down here.

364
00:17:42.452 --> 00:17:45.454
Leyla?

365
00:17:45.455 --> 00:17:50.807
♪♪

366
00:17:50.808 --> 00:17:52.896
Can you get out?

367
00:17:52.897 --> 00:17:54.637
It's a tar pit.

368
00:17:54.638 --> 00:17:56.639
I can't move.

369
00:17:56.640 --> 00:17:58.077
♪♪

370
00:18:01.602 --> 00:18:03.211
[dramatic music]

371
00:18:03.212 --> 00:18:04.517
Stop.

372
00:18:04.518 --> 00:18:05.866
Struggling is only going
to make you sink faster.

373
00:18:05.867 --> 00:18:07.259
What am I supposed to do?

374
00:18:07.260 --> 00:18:13.917
♪♪

375
00:18:13.918 --> 00:18:15.615
You're not strong enough
to get me out yourself.

376
00:18:15.616 --> 00:18:17.791
Go back to the fort
and get help.

377
00:18:17.792 --> 00:18:19.793
Izzy. you're not going to pull
me out with a dead branch.

378
00:18:19.794 --> 00:18:21.751
There's boars all
over here. right?

379
00:18:21.752 --> 00:18:24.145
And saber-tooths. and dinosaurs
and who knows what else.

380
00:18:24.146 --> 00:18:25.494
So leave me my bow.

381
00:18:25.495 --> 00:18:27.148
You taught me. you can't
fire without leverage.

382
00:18:27.149 --> 00:18:29.019
You're a sitting duck right now.

383
00:18:29.020 --> 00:18:30.978
There's no way I'm leaving you.

384
00:18:30.979 --> 00:18:33.459
Take it.

385
00:18:33.460 --> 00:18:35.853
Don't fall in. too.

386
00:18:39.944 --> 00:18:41.598
You ready?

387
00:18:42.599 --> 00:18:45.515
[grunting]

388
00:19:09.365 --> 00:19:10.583
You said it would take a while

389
00:19:10.584 --> 00:19:12.106
for our groups to begin to mesh.

390
00:19:12.107 --> 00:19:14.283
but I'm starting
to see progress.

391
00:19:19.332 --> 00:19:21.724
Me as well.

392
00:19:21.725 --> 00:19:23.552
A lot of that's thanks to you.

393
00:19:23.553 --> 00:19:26.381
Oh. all I try to do
is figure out how to turn

394
00:19:26.382 --> 00:19:29.341
obstacles into opportunities.

395
00:19:29.342 --> 00:19:31.038
Sounds like something
Lucas would say.

396
00:19:31.039 --> 00:19:32.866
- Really?
- Yeah.

397
00:19:32.867 --> 00:19:37.610
Actually. I think
I see a bit of you in him.

398
00:19:37.611 --> 00:19:41.527
the same calm under pressure.
the same ability

399
00:19:41.528 --> 00:19:43.006
to get along with everyone.

400
00:19:43.007 --> 00:19:47.054
The same desire to sit
on the Leadership Council?

401
00:19:47.055 --> 00:19:49.622
Mm.

402
00:19:49.623 --> 00:19:51.580
I know what you are doing.

403
00:19:51.581 --> 00:19:54.409
It's only fair that we
have a voice on the Council.

404
00:19:54.410 --> 00:19:57.064
And I'm only pushing Lucas
because he'd

405
00:19:57.065 --> 00:19:58.108
be good at the job.

406
00:19:58.109 --> 00:20:00.546
But also you love him.

407
00:20:00.547 --> 00:20:05.246
and love blinds people.

408
00:20:05.247 --> 00:20:07.510
Not when it comes to this.

409
00:20:08.859 --> 00:20:12.166
Lucas isn't who anyone
expected would lead us.

410
00:20:12.167 --> 00:20:13.515
When he first showed up here.

411
00:20:13.516 --> 00:20:15.387
he wasn't
the best person at all.

412
00:20:15.388 --> 00:20:18.477
But then he made
a decision to change.

413
00:20:18.478 --> 00:20:20.958
to be more than what he was.

414
00:20:22.133 --> 00:20:24.787
With your help.

415
00:20:24.788 --> 00:20:26.267
Yeah.

416
00:20:26.268 --> 00:20:29.052
I helped him live what he said.

417
00:20:29.053 --> 00:20:35.058
And then I watched him grow
into a person who everyone

418
00:20:35.059 --> 00:20:36.930
agreed should speak for us.

419
00:20:36.931 --> 00:20:40.499
He's fair.
he's honest. and he wants

420
00:20:40.500 --> 00:20:42.240
what's best for everyone.

421
00:20:42.241 --> 00:20:45.548
That's the kind of person you
should want on your Council.

422
00:20:47.376 --> 00:20:49.595
It is fascinating
to learn how a person

423
00:20:49.596 --> 00:20:52.467
finds the means to grow.

424
00:20:52.468 --> 00:20:55.688
Thank you
for sharing your story.

425
00:20:55.689 --> 00:20:57.995
Mm-hmm.

426
00:20:59.780 --> 00:21:01.651
Veronica?

427
00:21:04.175 --> 00:21:07.788
Actually. there is something
else I'd like to discuss.

428
00:21:09.485 --> 00:21:11.791
Even if you get
that fire started.

429
00:21:11.792 --> 00:21:13.445
the hunting party's
two valleys away by now.

430
00:21:13.446 --> 00:21:14.489
They're not going to see it.

431
00:21:14.490 --> 00:21:16.752
Stop.
You're making me nervous.

432
00:21:16.753 --> 00:21:18.537
What do you want me to do. then?

433
00:21:18.538 --> 00:21:21.148
I don't know.
Just talk about something else.

434
00:21:21.149 --> 00:21:23.411
I don't want to talk
about something else.

435
00:21:23.412 --> 00:21:24.978
Fine.

436
00:21:24.979 --> 00:21:27.589
I'll ask you a question.

437
00:21:27.590 --> 00:21:29.679
How many boar have you killed?

438
00:21:32.378 --> 00:21:34.031
None.

439
00:21:35.511 --> 00:21:37.338
I thought you were a great shot.

440
00:21:37.339 --> 00:21:39.514
I am.

441
00:21:39.515 --> 00:21:42.692
But maybe I'm scared to miss.

442
00:21:46.392 --> 00:21:49.350
What if I don't hit it.

443
00:21:49.351 --> 00:21:52.571
and that proves my mother right?

444
00:21:52.572 --> 00:21:55.356
I shouldn't be a warrior.

445
00:21:55.357 --> 00:21:58.141
I don't want to live in a box
that anyone makes for me.

446
00:21:58.142 --> 00:22:00.709
I get it.

447
00:22:00.710 --> 00:22:02.494
I spent a lot of time fighting
against the same thing

448
00:22:02.495 --> 00:22:04.148
back home.

449
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:09.371
I'm kind of an outsider. too.

450
00:22:11.025 --> 00:22:14.027
I did have one person
that got me.

451
00:22:14.028 --> 00:22:15.986
but then I lost him.

452
00:22:17.248 --> 00:22:18.379
Your boyfriend?

453
00:22:18.380 --> 00:22:21.470
No. my brother.

454
00:22:23.864 --> 00:22:25.865
My twin.

455
00:22:25.866 --> 00:22:28.564
We were completely inseparable.

456
00:22:29.652 --> 00:22:31.914
What happened to him?

457
00:22:31.915 --> 00:22:35.571
A few months ago.
a sickness came over the fort.

458
00:22:36.703 --> 00:22:41.621
My brother
and my father passed away.

459
00:22:43.971 --> 00:22:46.015
My brother told me
I was destined

460
00:22:46.016 --> 00:22:48.584
to become a great hunter.

461
00:22:50.760 --> 00:22:54.372
I wanted to come back
with a boar so he could see me.

462
00:22:54.373 --> 00:22:56.766
so he could be proud.

463
00:22:58.115 --> 00:23:01.161
Whenever I doubted myself
or others doubted me.

464
00:23:01.162 --> 00:23:02.249
he would say...

465
00:23:02.250 --> 00:23:03.947
Screw them?

466
00:23:05.601 --> 00:23:07.515
Something like that.

467
00:23:07.516 --> 00:23:11.737
♪♪

468
00:23:11.738 --> 00:23:16.830
That's why I wanted
to hunt a boar today.

469
00:23:18.048 --> 00:23:20.529
That's why I have
something to prove.

470
00:23:26.666 --> 00:23:29.145
No. we don't have time for fire.

471
00:23:29.146 --> 00:23:36.415
♪♪

472
00:23:37.067 --> 00:23:39.547
<i>♪♪ There's a bottle
in the cupboard ♪♪</i>

473
00:23:39.548 --> 00:23:42.811
<i>♪♪ Up on the top shelf</i>

474
00:23:42.812 --> 00:23:44.553
Hey.

475
00:23:46.512 --> 00:23:48.077
I just got your message.

476
00:23:48.078 --> 00:23:49.514
Thank God you found him.

477
00:23:49.515 --> 00:23:50.950
Did you talk to him?

478
00:23:50.951 --> 00:23:52.778
Did you ask if he could
get us on the base?

479
00:23:52.779 --> 00:23:55.781
Yeah. I tried.
He's not listening.

480
00:23:55.782 --> 00:23:57.827
Maybe you'll have better luck.

481
00:24:01.657 --> 00:24:05.007
Hey. can I get
a scotch neat. please?

482
00:24:05.008 --> 00:24:08.315
You're going to try and bribe
me with a drink now. huh?

483
00:24:08.316 --> 00:24:10.099
No.

484
00:24:10.100 --> 00:24:12.101
This one's for me.

485
00:24:12.102 --> 00:24:14.495
Nothing you can do
is going to change my mind.

486
00:24:14.496 --> 00:24:15.844
Besides. there's
nothing in my mind

487
00:24:15.845 --> 00:24:17.629
that can help you. anyway.

488
00:24:17.630 --> 00:24:19.065
What I think this
is really about

489
00:24:19.066 --> 00:24:20.762
is your fear of facing
a painful part of your life.

490
00:24:20.763 --> 00:24:24.550
But I'm done trying
to convince you.

491
00:24:30.425 --> 00:24:32.426
Excuse me.
Another one. please.

492
00:24:32.427 --> 00:24:33.862
You know. you say
you have it bad.

493
00:24:33.863 --> 00:24:36.082
And to be fair. you do.

494
00:24:36.083 --> 00:24:39.825
But for me. being back
here. all it's done

495
00:24:39.826 --> 00:24:43.481
is forced me to relive every
awful mistake I've made.

496
00:24:43.482 --> 00:24:46.353
And what's worse. no matter
how hard I try to fix

497
00:24:46.354 --> 00:24:49.662
those mistakes. I can't.

498
00:24:53.666 --> 00:24:56.537
What kind of mistakes?

499
00:24:56.538 --> 00:25:02.325
My ex-wife. she relied heavily

500
00:25:02.326 --> 00:25:06.025
on alcohol and pills.

501
00:25:06.026 --> 00:25:09.985
Over the course of our divorce.
it all started up again.

502
00:25:09.986 --> 00:25:13.947
My life was ending. and I
allowed that to swallow hers.

503
00:25:18.125 --> 00:25:20.953
Tonight. Sophie
will try to fight

504
00:25:20.954 --> 00:25:23.521
her demons at an AA meeting.

505
00:25:23.522 --> 00:25:25.044
It won't work.

506
00:25:25.045 --> 00:25:27.916
She'll walk out
into the parking lot.

507
00:25:27.917 --> 00:25:30.963
drink a fifth of vodka.
get in her car.

508
00:25:30.964 --> 00:25:35.097
and accidentally blindside
a young family's SUV.

509
00:25:35.098 --> 00:25:37.796
The father will
slip into a coma.

510
00:25:37.797 --> 00:25:40.450
- What happens to him?
- I don't know.

511
00:25:40.451 --> 00:25:43.715
He was still in the coma
when I fell in the sinkhole.

512
00:25:43.716 --> 00:25:46.587
What I do know is
that my mistakes have

513
00:25:46.588 --> 00:25:49.285
left a path of destruction.

514
00:25:49.286 --> 00:25:54.464
I broke a good woman's heart.
and it ruined her life.

515
00:25:54.465 --> 00:25:57.467
[soft music]

516
00:25:57.468 --> 00:26:02.168
♪♪

517
00:26:02.169 --> 00:26:04.649
You should tell her
what you know.

518
00:26:04.650 --> 00:26:07.304
Me as the messenger
is the problem.

519
00:26:08.131 --> 00:26:11.700
Maybe when it comes
to you as well.

520
00:26:13.963 --> 00:26:17.836
You're being a coward. Gavin.

521
00:26:17.837 --> 00:26:19.489
I'm trying to get you
back to your family.

522
00:26:19.490 --> 00:26:22.319
but it's never going to happen
if you're sitting here.

523
00:26:24.365 --> 00:26:27.759
All I need to know is.
are you ready to face

524
00:26:27.760 --> 00:26:30.370
your fears or not?

525
00:26:30.371 --> 00:26:33.373
[dramatic music]

526
00:26:33.374 --> 00:26:39.205
♪♪

527
00:26:39.206 --> 00:26:42.165
[birds chirping]

528
00:26:54.482 --> 00:26:56.004
This should be enough.

529
00:26:56.005 --> 00:26:58.746
Care to explain why
you're picking mushrooms?

530
00:26:58.747 --> 00:27:01.836
What I've picked is poison.

531
00:27:01.837 --> 00:27:04.099
Ingest too much. and you'll
slip into cardiac arrest.

532
00:27:04.100 --> 00:27:06.058
but native people
have been using

533
00:27:06.059 --> 00:27:08.756
this fungus for centuries
to open their minds.

534
00:27:08.757 --> 00:27:11.019
Great.
So you want to get me high.

535
00:27:11.020 --> 00:27:13.065
I want to expand
your mind and guide

536
00:27:13.066 --> 00:27:14.849
you to the memories you lost.

537
00:27:14.850 --> 00:27:16.285
I'm a doctor.

538
00:27:16.286 --> 00:27:17.809
I'm going to need more
than a caveman version

539
00:27:17.810 --> 00:27:19.680
of "Fear and Loathing
in Las Vegas."

540
00:27:19.681 --> 00:27:21.290
In my line of work. I've used it

541
00:27:21.291 --> 00:27:24.163
and other drugs
like it extensively.

542
00:27:24.164 --> 00:27:26.818
What exactly is it that you do?

543
00:27:26.819 --> 00:27:28.907
I'm a PSYOPs officer
in the Air Force.

544
00:27:28.908 --> 00:27:31.997
Essentially. my job is
to manipulate behavior.

545
00:27:31.998 --> 00:27:35.696
I've done it for ill. but
now I want to do it for good.

546
00:27:35.697 --> 00:27:38.264
This will just take a minute.

547
00:27:38.265 --> 00:27:45.228
♪♪

548
00:27:46.665 --> 00:27:49.449
Hey. you up for this?

549
00:27:49.450 --> 00:27:51.844
That drug could be dangerous.

550
00:27:53.584 --> 00:27:55.237
Yeah. it could be.

551
00:27:55.238 --> 00:27:56.935
But. Sam.
if this woman can help me

552
00:27:56.936 --> 00:27:58.110
see something
that will get Eve back.

553
00:27:58.111 --> 00:28:00.242
I got to take that chance.

554
00:28:00.243 --> 00:28:04.029
♪♪

555
00:28:04.030 --> 00:28:06.248
It's ready if you are.

556
00:28:06.249 --> 00:28:13.256
♪♪

557
00:28:31.361 --> 00:28:33.798
[horses snorting]

558
00:28:33.799 --> 00:28:35.801
OK. good boy.

559
00:28:37.977 --> 00:28:40.240
- Hey.
- Hey.

560
00:28:43.112 --> 00:28:44.634
What was that for?

561
00:28:44.635 --> 00:28:46.811
I thought you had
a thing for stable boys.

562
00:28:46.812 --> 00:28:48.682
Hm.

563
00:28:48.683 --> 00:28:50.902
You OK?

564
00:28:50.903 --> 00:28:52.817
I got to tell you something.

565
00:28:52.818 --> 00:28:54.209
Uh-oh.

566
00:28:54.210 --> 00:28:56.212
That doesn't sound good.

567
00:28:57.300 --> 00:29:01.174
Ruth is impressed with you.

568
00:29:02.436 --> 00:29:05.786
But she's also
impressed with me.

569
00:29:05.787 --> 00:29:08.223
OK.

570
00:29:08.224 --> 00:29:11.052
She offered me the Council seat.

571
00:29:11.053 --> 00:29:13.707
Why would she do that?

572
00:29:13.708 --> 00:29:16.884
I told you.
she's impressed with me.

573
00:29:16.885 --> 00:29:19.582
Is that so hard to believe?

574
00:29:19.583 --> 00:29:21.149
I mean. no. of course not.

575
00:29:21.150 --> 00:29:22.716
You're amazing.

576
00:29:22.717 --> 00:29:26.676
I'm just wondering why she
chose you out of the blue.

577
00:29:26.677 --> 00:29:29.679
Look. I know what
this means to you.

578
00:29:29.680 --> 00:29:31.159
but you don't need
to be on the Council

579
00:29:31.160 --> 00:29:32.378
to get everyone's respect.

580
00:29:32.379 --> 00:29:34.554
- You already have that.
- OK. I know that.

581
00:29:34.555 --> 00:29:37.470
So then why can't you
just be happy for me?

582
00:29:37.471 --> 00:29:38.819
Veronica. I'm sorry.

583
00:29:38.820 --> 00:29:40.255
I am happy for you.

584
00:29:40.256 --> 00:29:41.779
OK.

585
00:29:41.780 --> 00:29:43.998
I am.

586
00:29:43.999 --> 00:29:47.480
We don't need to talk
about this anymore.

587
00:29:47.481 --> 00:29:49.221
Ruth wanted me to meet
the rest of the Council.

588
00:29:49.222 --> 00:29:51.484
so I'll see you later. OK?

589
00:29:51.485 --> 00:29:54.443
[tense music]

590
00:29:54.444 --> 00:30:01.625
♪♪

591
00:30:08.589 --> 00:30:10.764
I think it's almost
long enough to reach you.

592
00:30:10.765 --> 00:30:11.852
Hang in there.

593
00:30:11.853 --> 00:30:14.724
[animal growls]

594
00:30:14.725 --> 00:30:17.031
We gotta get you out of there.

595
00:30:17.032 --> 00:30:19.904
[dramatic music]

596
00:30:19.905 --> 00:30:23.603
♪♪

597
00:30:23.604 --> 00:30:25.039
OK.

598
00:30:25.040 --> 00:30:26.998
Come on. Keep going.

599
00:30:26.999 --> 00:30:29.391
Come on.

600
00:30:29.392 --> 00:30:31.307
Keep going.

601
00:30:32.482 --> 00:30:34.048
It's a boar!

602
00:30:34.049 --> 00:30:35.703
Get your bow.

603
00:30:37.096 --> 00:30:39.401
[boar squeals]

604
00:30:39.402 --> 00:30:46.583
♪♪

605
00:30:50.892 --> 00:30:53.460
Damn it.

606
00:31:06.952 --> 00:31:09.431
[laughs]

607
00:31:09.432 --> 00:31:11.390
- You did it.
- We did it.

608
00:31:11.391 --> 00:31:12.870
Yeah. we did.

609
00:31:12.871 --> 00:31:14.132
Mm.

610
00:31:14.133 --> 00:31:16.612
I need a bath.

611
00:31:16.613 --> 00:31:19.312
- A little bit. yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

612
00:31:28.016 --> 00:31:30.104
[applause]

613
00:31:30.105 --> 00:31:33.586
Thank you. Sara. for sharing.

614
00:31:33.587 --> 00:31:35.762
So it's time to wrap up.

615
00:31:35.763 --> 00:31:39.505
But first. I want
to acknowledge something.

616
00:31:39.506 --> 00:31:42.508
Sophie. we haven't seen
you in a few months.

617
00:31:42.509 --> 00:31:44.466
but you're here today.

618
00:31:44.467 --> 00:31:47.121
Care to share anything?

619
00:31:47.122 --> 00:31:49.645
No.

620
00:31:49.646 --> 00:31:52.300
- Not today.
- OK.

621
00:31:52.301 --> 00:31:54.869
I'd like to say a few words.

622
00:31:56.349 --> 00:31:58.959
Sorry.
it's been a while. but I...

623
00:31:58.960 --> 00:32:01.484
I felt like I had to come today.

624
00:32:13.018 --> 00:32:14.453
Hi.

625
00:32:14.454 --> 00:32:16.977
I'm Gavin. and I'm an alcoholic.

626
00:32:16.978 --> 00:32:19.024
All: Hi. Gavin.

627
00:32:20.721 --> 00:32:25.377
The last few years. I've
been hiding. not from anyone

628
00:32:25.378 --> 00:32:28.033
out there. but from myself.

629
00:32:29.556 --> 00:32:32.514
I've been hiding
in bars. alleys.

630
00:32:32.515 --> 00:32:34.864
anywhere there's alcohol.

631
00:32:34.865 --> 00:32:37.737
It's just easier than
facing my problems head on.

632
00:32:37.738 --> 00:32:40.827
Liquor makes us believe
the biggest lie we all

633
00:32:40.828 --> 00:32:43.830
have to face in this room.
that we're

634
00:32:43.831 --> 00:32:46.921
broken and can't be fixed.

635
00:32:49.750 --> 00:32:53.187
Recently.
somebody came into my life.

636
00:32:53.188 --> 00:32:57.410
and they said that they could
help get me back on track.

637
00:32:59.194 --> 00:33:01.804
But I didn't believe them.

638
00:33:01.805 --> 00:33:05.373
In fact. when they said
the words that I needed help.

639
00:33:05.374 --> 00:33:07.854
I got angry.

640
00:33:07.855 --> 00:33:10.726
I got scared.
and I did what I always do

641
00:33:10.727 --> 00:33:12.815
when help comes along.

642
00:33:12.816 --> 00:33:16.515
I ran.

643
00:33:16.516 --> 00:33:18.560
ran straight to the bottle.

644
00:33:18.561 --> 00:33:21.563
[soft music]

645
00:33:21.564 --> 00:33:24.697
♪♪

646
00:33:24.698 --> 00:33:27.308
And that person came back.

647
00:33:27.309 --> 00:33:30.050
And I think if you try
and knock someone down so hard.

648
00:33:30.051 --> 00:33:32.487
but they still come back
and try to help you.

649
00:33:32.488 --> 00:33:33.793
then I think you have to believe

650
00:33:33.794 --> 00:33:36.013
that that person gives a damn.

651
00:33:36.014 --> 00:33:39.277
Everyone in this room
needs someone

652
00:33:39.278 --> 00:33:41.932
who gives a damn...

653
00:33:44.587 --> 00:33:47.241
As none of us
can do it on our own.

654
00:33:47.242 --> 00:33:52.420
♪♪

655
00:33:52.421 --> 00:33:55.598
[applause]

656
00:33:59.907 --> 00:34:01.951
Hey.

657
00:34:01.952 --> 00:34:04.042
Can we talk?

658
00:34:06.261 --> 00:34:08.523
OK.

659
00:34:08.524 --> 00:34:15.705
♪♪

660
00:34:26.281 --> 00:34:31.633
Gavin. you're ready to
access the memories you lost.

661
00:34:31.634 --> 00:34:34.723
But we have to guide you
to the right one.

662
00:34:34.724 --> 00:34:38.118
You told me you got
a message about Eve.

663
00:34:38.119 --> 00:34:40.339
Where did it come from?

664
00:34:41.383 --> 00:34:46.126
It was a signal.
came through a double aurora.

665
00:34:46.127 --> 00:34:47.258
Good.

666
00:34:47.259 --> 00:34:48.650
I want you to focus on that.

667
00:34:48.651 --> 00:34:50.784
Picture that aurora.

668
00:34:54.788 --> 00:34:56.571
What else does it trigger?

669
00:34:56.572 --> 00:34:59.574
[dramatic music]

670
00:34:59.575 --> 00:35:06.713
♪♪

671
00:35:14.460 --> 00:35:16.200
Gavin. are you all right?

672
00:35:16.201 --> 00:35:17.898
Gavin?

673
00:35:19.291 --> 00:35:21.727
Help me steady him.

674
00:35:21.728 --> 00:35:23.468
Gavin. Gavin.

675
00:35:23.469 --> 00:35:24.731
Gavin!

676
00:35:28.300 --> 00:35:31.040
[tense music]

677
00:35:31.041 --> 00:35:36.916
♪♪

678
00:35:36.917 --> 00:35:38.700
Let him rest.

679
00:35:38.701 --> 00:35:40.398
That's what he needs right now.

680
00:35:40.399 --> 00:35:42.008
OK.

681
00:35:42.009 --> 00:35:49.147
♪♪

682
00:36:02.551 --> 00:36:04.379
Hey.

683
00:36:05.685 --> 00:36:07.468
How's your dad?

684
00:36:07.469 --> 00:36:08.861
He's asleep.

685
00:36:08.862 --> 00:36:11.211
Sam says he's going to be OK.

686
00:36:11.212 --> 00:36:13.300
What about you?

687
00:36:13.301 --> 00:36:16.173
Much better now that
I got the tar off.

688
00:36:16.174 --> 00:36:18.610
Really glad you had
that baby powder stuff.

689
00:36:18.611 --> 00:36:20.568
Worked miracles.

690
00:36:20.569 --> 00:36:22.222
Where did you learn that?

691
00:36:22.223 --> 00:36:24.138
From the internet.

692
00:36:27.315 --> 00:36:29.491
I'll explain later.

693
00:36:31.493 --> 00:36:34.016
I never got to thank you
for staying with me

694
00:36:34.017 --> 00:36:36.236
and keeping me safe.

695
00:36:36.237 --> 00:36:38.325
You don't have to.

696
00:36:38.326 --> 00:36:40.023
I do.

697
00:36:41.286 --> 00:36:44.332
It's really nice
to have someone who cares.

698
00:36:46.813 --> 00:36:50.990
You do feel that way. right?

699
00:36:50.991 --> 00:36:52.992
I do.

700
00:36:52.993 --> 00:36:55.951
[soft music]

701
00:36:55.952 --> 00:37:01.174
♪♪

702
00:37:01.175 --> 00:37:03.002
I thought so.

703
00:37:03.003 --> 00:37:09.182
♪♪

704
00:37:09.183 --> 00:37:12.360
[laughter]

705
00:37:27.984 --> 00:37:29.942
Whoa. whoa. Take it easy.

706
00:37:29.943 --> 00:37:31.248
What happened?

707
00:37:31.249 --> 00:37:33.293
You scared the hell out of us.

708
00:37:33.294 --> 00:37:36.165
You've been out for hours.

709
00:37:36.166 --> 00:37:38.430
How are you feeling?

710
00:37:41.563 --> 00:37:43.825
Sam. I feel like
a ten-beer hangover.

711
00:37:43.826 --> 00:37:46.699
Did it work?
You get back any memories?

712
00:37:48.483 --> 00:37:52.356
Yeah. I saw something.
a double aurora.

713
00:37:52.357 --> 00:37:53.966
And there was a safe.

714
00:37:53.967 --> 00:37:55.228
I opened it.

715
00:37:55.229 --> 00:37:57.491
What was inside?

716
00:37:57.492 --> 00:37:59.276
Um...

717
00:37:59.277 --> 00:38:02.279
[dramatic music]

718
00:38:02.280 --> 00:38:06.152
♪♪

719
00:38:06.153 --> 00:38:07.632
<i>There was some
kind of microchip.</i>

720
00:38:07.633 --> 00:38:09.590
<i>and I think I was stealing it.</i>

721
00:38:09.591 --> 00:38:12.680
♪♪

722
00:38:12.681 --> 00:38:14.378
But nothing about Eve or where

723
00:38:14.379 --> 00:38:15.683
she could be. how to find her?

724
00:38:15.684 --> 00:38:19.297
No. no. no. no. no.
It was just a chip.

725
00:38:20.994 --> 00:38:22.735
What do you think that means?

726
00:38:25.303 --> 00:38:27.260
Maybe whoever sent
that message was never

727
00:38:27.261 --> 00:38:29.306
trying to help us find Eve.

728
00:38:29.307 --> 00:38:30.742
Could be they only
want the information

729
00:38:30.743 --> 00:38:32.221
inside of your head.

730
00:38:32.222 --> 00:38:34.789
And they just wanted
the microchip all along.

731
00:38:34.790 --> 00:38:39.577
♪♪

732
00:38:39.578 --> 00:38:41.230
Look. I...

733
00:38:41.231 --> 00:38:46.366
I think some time in rehab is
what I really need right now.

734
00:38:46.367 --> 00:38:49.414
You have no idea how
happy that makes me.

735
00:38:51.154 --> 00:38:56.028
Sophie. I am sorry
about everything.

736
00:38:56.029 --> 00:38:59.161
I know we didn't work out.
but I wouldn't be the man

737
00:38:59.162 --> 00:39:00.816
I am today without you.

738
00:39:02.992 --> 00:39:06.125
I'm sorry I can't do
anything to help you.

739
00:39:06.126 --> 00:39:07.735
I know you don't have much time.

740
00:39:07.736 --> 00:39:11.478
No. I'm actually hopeful
in that department.

741
00:39:11.479 --> 00:39:14.395
taking something experimental.

742
00:39:16.049 --> 00:39:20.269
But I need you to focus
on your better place.

743
00:39:20.270 --> 00:39:26.233
You deserve love and happiness.

744
00:39:27.539 --> 00:39:30.279
You need to promise me
you'll keep writing.

745
00:39:30.280 --> 00:39:32.804
Do you really think
it's worth it?

746
00:39:32.805 --> 00:39:34.894
I do.

747
00:39:36.417 --> 00:39:39.202
Thank you. Ty.

748
00:39:42.075 --> 00:39:44.816
Be well. Soph.

749
00:39:44.817 --> 00:39:51.780
♪♪

750
00:40:00.963 --> 00:40:03.008
So what did Sophie say?

751
00:40:03.009 --> 00:40:05.924
I think Gavin's speech made
her see things differently.

752
00:40:05.925 --> 00:40:07.839
I just said what I felt.

753
00:40:07.840 --> 00:40:10.363
Well. what I heard made me
think you're ready to take

754
00:40:10.364 --> 00:40:12.974
a step forward. too.

755
00:40:12.975 --> 00:40:15.412
I am.

756
00:40:15.413 --> 00:40:16.978
If there's a way
to get us onto the base.

757
00:40:16.979 --> 00:40:18.720
I'm going to find it.

758
00:40:20.113 --> 00:40:21.200
That's the Gavin I know.

759
00:40:21.201 --> 00:40:22.549
All right.

760
00:40:22.550 --> 00:40:24.377
Let's say we get out of here
and talk next steps.

761
00:40:24.378 --> 00:40:25.639
Yeah. works for me.

762
00:40:25.640 --> 00:40:27.772
Let's do it
over a coffee this time.

763
00:40:27.773 --> 00:40:29.469
Yeah.

764
00:40:29.470 --> 00:40:36.608
♪♪

765
00:41:04.723 --> 00:41:07.464
[dramatic music]

766
00:41:07.465 --> 00:41:14.602
♪♪

766
00:41:15.305 --> 00:42:15.862
